01/11/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Authorities announced on Wednesday (October 31st) that a cocaine smuggling ring was smashed by an international operation involving Croatian police.
A total of 23 people were arrested, ten of them Croatian citizens.
The operation started at the beginning of this year.
The criminal gang is suspected of having sold at least 200kg of cocaine, valued at 8m euros since 2000.
The operation was conducted by authorities in Croatia, Germany, Italy, Luxembourg and the Netherlands.
(HRT, AFP - 31/10/07)
